# ─── caddy-x402avm end-to-end test environment ───────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values, then run:
#
#   go test ./testscenario/ -v -timeout 3m -run TestWeatherAPIPaywall
#
# Prerequisites
# ─────────────
# 1. Build the caddy binary with the x402 plugin:
#      make build
#
# 2. CLIENT_MNEMONIC account requirements (Algorand testnet):
#    - Must be opted into testnet USDC: ASA ID 10458941
#    - Must hold enough testnet USDC to pay (0.001 USDC per test run)
#    - Must hold enough testnet ALGO to cover transaction fees (~0.002 ALGO)
#    Get testnet USDC from: https://testnet.folks.finance/ (USDC dispenser)
#    Get testnet ALGO from: https://bank.testnet.algorand.network/
#
# 3. PAY_TO address requirements (Algorand testnet):
#    - Must be opted into testnet USDC: ASA ID 10458941
#    - Can be the same as CLIENT_MNEMONIC's address or a separate operator address
#
# 4. To find your address from the mnemonic:
#      goal account import -m "your 25 words here"
#    or use any Algorand wallet that supports testnet.

# 25-word Algorand mnemonic of the account that will pay for API calls.
CLIENT_MNEMONIC=word1 word2 word3 word4 word5 word6 word7 word8 word9 word10 word11 word12 word13 word14 word15 word16 word17 word18 word19 word20 word21 word22 word23 word24 word25

# Algorand testnet address that receives the $0.001 USDC micropayments.
# This is the "merchant" wallet – the API operator's address.
PAY_TO=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA
